<div data-controller="appear">
  <h1 class="type-display-punjabi text-center animate-fade-in-up" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">Explore Orange County</h1>
  <p class="text-center animate-fade-in-up delay-1" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); max-width: 40rem; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
    You're in Southern California for Thanksgiving weekend — make the most of it.
  </p>
  <p class="text-center animate-fade-in-up delay-2" style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-12); max-width: 40rem; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
    Thursday is a free day. Here are some of our favorite spots in the area.
  </p>

  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div class="card appear">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">Disneyland & Disney California Adventure</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Walking distance from JW Marriott · Anaheim, CA</p>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          The JW Marriott is literally next door to the Happiest Place on Earth. Whether you're a first-timer or a regular, a day at Disneyland or California Adventure is a perfect way to spend Thanksgiving. Buy tickets in advance — the parks fill up fast over the holiday weekend.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card appear appear-delay-1">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">Knott's Berry Farm</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">~10 minutes · Buena Park, CA (near the Gurudwara)</p>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          America's oldest theme park. Great for thrill rides, funnel cake, and a more relaxed vibe than Disneyland. It's right by Singh Sabha Gurudwara in Buena Park — easy to combine with a pre-ceremony visit to the neighborhood on Thursday.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card appear appear-delay-2">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">Artesia — Little India</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">~20 minutes · Artesia, CA</p>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          Southern California's South Asian hub. Pioneer Boulevard is lined with Indian and Pakistani restaurants, sweet shops, jewelry stores, and fabric boutiques. Ideal for picking up last-minute wedding attire, loading up on mithai, or just grabbing a proper chai and paratha. Highly recommend if you haven't been.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card appear">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">Newport Beach & Balboa Island</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">~30 minutes · Newport Beach, CA</p>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          One of Orange County's most beautiful coastal towns. Walk the Balboa Peninsula, grab a famous Balboa Bar ice cream, or just sit on the beach and enjoy the Pacific. The harbor is stunning, and there's no shortage of great restaurants nearby.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card appear appear-delay-1">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">Huntington Beach (Surf City USA)</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">~25 minutes · Huntington Beach, CA</p>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          Wide, sandy, quintessentially SoCal. Walk the pier, rent a bike along the strand, or just find a spot to relax. The downtown area has good food and coffee within walking distance of the beach.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card appear appear-delay-2">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">Old Town Orange</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">~15 minutes · Orange, CA</p>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          A charming historic downtown built around a traffic circle — one of the only intact historic downtowns in SoCal. Great for antique shops, local restaurants, coffee, and a slow afternoon walk. A nice contrast to the theme parks.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card appear">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">Downtown Anaheim / The Packing District</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">~10 minutes · Anaheim, CA</p>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          Anaheim's local food scene centered around a converted 1920s packinghouse. Food halls, local vendors, craft beer, and a farmers market on Thursdays and Saturdays. A great spot for breakfast or a casual lunch away from the resort area.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
